humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The report indicates that the patient has pNO sn (n=3), which means that there were no metastatic carcinomas found in the assessed lymph nodes (N0) and that 3 lymph nodes were assessed (sn). This matches New Rule 11 and New Rule 1, and thus the N stage is N0.

humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The 'pNO' in the tumor classification indicates that there is no evidence of cancer in the regional lymph nodes (N0) based on the examination of 3 sentinel lymph nodes (n=3). This is the correct answer, so the options N1, N2, and N3 are not applicable in this case.
